# ============================================
# DONATION BOOK - Environment Variables
# ============================================
# 
# This is a MULTI-FESTIVAL application with comprehensive features:
# - Multiple independent festivals with unique codes
# - Per-festival passwords (user & admin)
# - Per-festival theming (colors, backgrounds)
# - Showcase feature with albums and media (photos, videos, PDFs, audio)
# - Storage management with 400MB limit per festival
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to '.env.local'
# 2. Fill in your Supabase credentials
# 3. Run the required SQL migrations in order
# 4. Create a 'showcase' storage bucket in Supabase
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env.local to version control!
#

# ============================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (REQUIRED)
# ============================================
#
# To get these values:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com and sign in
# 2. Select your project (or create a new one)
# 3. Go to Settings > API
# 4. Copy the values below
#

# Your Supabase Project URL
# Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here

# Your Supabase Anonymous (Public) Key
# Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here


# ============================================
# DATABASE SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================
#
# Run these SQL files IN ORDER in your Supabase SQL Editor:
#
# 1. supabase-schema.sql (Base schema - optional, for reference)
# 2. supabase-migration-multifestive.sql (REQUIRED - Multi-festival support)
# 3. supabase-migration-showcase.sql (REQUIRED - Showcase/Albums feature)
# 4. supabase-add-time-fields.sql (REQUIRED - Time tracking for collections/expenses)
# 5. supabase-storage-fix.sql (REQUIRED - Storage bucket permissions)
#
# After running migrations, verify:
# - 'festivals' table exists
# - 'albums' and 'media_items' tables exist
# - All tables have 'festival_id' column
# - Storage bucket 'showcase' exists and is public
#

# ============================================
# STORAGE BUCKET SETUP (REQUIRED FOR SHOWCASE)
# ============================================
#
# 1. In Supabase dashboard, go to Storage
# 2. Click "New Bucket"
# 3. Name: 'showcase'
# 4. Make it PUBLIC (toggle on)
# 5. Click "Create Bucket"
# 6. Run 'supabase-storage-fix.sql' to set permissions
#
# Storage Limits (enforced in app):
# - Photos/PDFs/Audio: 15MB per file
# - Videos: 50MB per file
# - Total per festival: 400MB
#

# ============================================
# APPLICATION FEATURES
# ============================================
#
# MULTI-FESTIVAL SYSTEM:
# - Each festival has a unique 8-character code (e.g., ABCD1234)
# - Access via: /f/[code]
# - Create new festivals at: /create
# - View existing festivals at: /view
#
# PER-FESTIVAL FEATURES:
# - Independent data (collections, expenses, groups, categories)
# - Custom passwords (user & admin)
# - Custom theme (7 colors + background image + dark mode)
# - Showcase albums with media uploads
# - 400MB storage limit per festival
#
# AUTHENTICATION:
# - User password: Optional, per-festival, daily session
# - Admin password: Per-festival, URL param access
# - Sessions expire daily at midnight
# - Auto-logout when passwords are changed
#
# SHOWCASE FEATURES:
# - Create albums with cover photos
# - Upload photos, videos, PDFs, audio files
# - View media in full-screen modal
# - Download individual files or multiple selections
# - Storage usage tracking with detailed breakdown
# - File size limits: 15MB (images/PDFs/audio), 50MB (videos)
# - Upload queue system for multiple files
# - Live upload progress with file count
# - Preview thumbnails for all media types
#

# ============================================
# DEFAULT CREDENTIALS (PER FESTIVAL)
# ============================================
#
# When creating a new festival, you set:
# - User password (optional, can be disabled)
# - Admin password (required)
#
# Example defaults you might use:
# USER PASSWORD: Festive@123 (or any password you choose)
# ADMIN PASSWORD: admin (or any password you choose)
#
# Note: Each festival has its own passwords!
# Festival A can have different passwords than Festival B
#
# Admin URL format: /f/[CODE]/admin?p=[admin_password]
# Example: /f/ABCD1234/admin?p=admin
#

# ============================================
# ROUTING STRUCTURE
# ============================================
#
# Landing & Entry:
# / - Superhome landing page
# /view - Enter festival code to view
# /create - Create new festival
#
# Festival Pages (requires code):
# /f/[code] - Festival dashboard
# /f/[code]/collection - Collections with charts
# /f/[code]/expense - Expenses with charts
# /f/[code]/transaction - Combined transactions
# /f/[code]/showcase - Albums and media gallery
# /f/[code]/admin - Admin panel (requires admin password)
#

# ============================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================
#
# "Supabase credentials not found":
# - Check this file is named '.env.local' (not .env.local.txt)
# - Verify values have no extra spaces
# - Restart development server: npm run dev
#
# "Failed to fetch data":
# - Verify Supabase project is active
# - Check all migrations were run successfully
# - Confirm API credentials are correct
# - Check browser console for specific errors
#
# "Storage upload failed":
# - Verify 'showcase' bucket exists in Supabase Storage
# - Check bucket is set to PUBLIC
# - Run 'supabase-storage-fix.sql' for permissions
# - Verify file size is within limits (15MB/50MB)
#
# "Password not working":
# - Each festival has its own passwords
# - Check you're using the correct festival code
# - Passwords are case-sensitive
# - Admin password can be changed in admin panel
# - Sessions expire daily - re-enter password next day
#
# "Storage limit exceeded":
# - Each festival has 400MB total storage
# - Check storage usage in admin panel (click storage bar)
# - Delete unused media to free up space
# - Consider creating a new festival for new events
#

# ============================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
# ============================================
#
# When deploying to Vercel, Netlify, Railway, etc.:
#
# 1. Add environment variables in platform dashboard:
#    - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
#    - NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# 2. Ensure all SQL migrations are run in production Supabase
#
# 3. Create 'showcase' storage bucket in production
#
# 4. DO NOT commit .env.local to repository
#
# 5. Set up custom domain (optional)
#
# 6. Configure CORS in Supabase if needed
#

# ============================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================
#
# Current Implementation (Community/Small Group Use):
# - Client-side password protection
# - Public Supabase RLS policies
# - Passwords stored in plain text in database
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix makes variables accessible in browser
#
# This is suitable for:
# - Small communities (hostels, clubs)
# - Trusted user groups
# - Non-sensitive financial data
# - Festival/event tracking
#
# For Production/Enterprise Use, Consider:
# - Implement Supabase Auth (email/password, OAuth)
# - Hash passwords (bcrypt, argon2)
# - Server-side API routes for sensitive operations
# - Row Level Security (RLS) with user authentication
# - Rate limiting on uploads
# - HTTPS only
# - Environment variable encryption
# - Audit logging
# - Regular security audits
#
# The NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is safe to expose:
# - It's designed to be public (client-side use)
# - RLS policies control data access
# - Never expose SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY in client code
#

# ============================================
# STORAGE MANAGEMENT
# ============================================
#
# Per-Festival Storage Limits:
# - Total: 400MB per festival
# - Photos: 15MB per file
# - Videos: 50MB per file
# - PDFs: 15MB per file
# - Audio: 15MB per file
#
# Storage Tracking:
# - View usage in admin panel (click storage bar)
# - See breakdown by media type (photos, videos, PDFs, audio)
# - See breakdown by album
# - Total files count and storage used
#
# Storage Cleanup:
# - Delete albums to free space
# - Delete individual media items
# - Cascade delete: Deleting album deletes all its media
#

# ============================================
# SHOWCASE FEATURE DETAILS
# ============================================
#
# Albums:
# - Create albums with title, description, year
# - Set cover photo for each album
# - Organize media by albums
#
