# ============================================
# QUICK START GUIDE
# ============================================
#
# 1. SETUP SUPABASE:
#    - Create project at supabase.com
#    - Copy URL and anon key to this file
#    - Save as .env.local
#
# 2. RUN MIGRATIONS:
#    - Open Supabase SQL Editor
#    - Run supabase-migration-multifestive.sql
#    - Run supabase-migration-showcase.sql
#    - Run supabase-add-time-fields.sql
#    - Run supabase-storage-fix.sql
#
# 3. CREATE STORAGE BUCKET:
#    - Go to Storage in Supabase
#    - Create bucket named 'showcase'
#    - Make it PUBLIC
#
# 4. START APP:
#    - Run: npm install
#    - Run: npm run dev
#    - Open: http://localhost:3000
#
# 5. CREATE FIRST FESTIVAL:
#    - Click "Create a Festival"
#    - Fill in details
#    - Set passwords
#    - Choose theme
#    - Get your unique code (e.g., ABCD1234)
#
# 6. SHARE WITH TEAM:
#    - Share URL: http://localhost:3000/f/ABCD1234
#    - Share user password (if enabled)
#    - Admin access: /f/ABCD1234/admin?p=admin
#
# 7. START USING:
#    - Add collections (donations)
#    - Add expenses
#    - Create showcase albums
#    - Upload photos/videos
#    - View analytics and charts
#

